<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
MHD_lookup_connection_value_n() returns a pointer to the header value (enc) but the API does not guarantee that the value is NUL-terminated unless the caller asked for the length and made a copy. The code calls MHD_str_equal_caseless_(enc, "chunked") which walks enc until it finds a '\0'. If the header value in pos->value is not NUL-terminated (common for headers stored with an associated length), MHD_str_equal_caseless_ will read beyond the bounds of the object referenced by enc, causing an out‑of‑bounds access. This violates the intent of MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17. A safe fix is to obtain the value length (pass a size_t pointer to MHD_lookup_connection_value_n) and use a length‑bounded comparison (e.g. MHD_str_equal_caseless_bin_n_ or compare up to val_len after checking lengths).
</scenario>
